quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  3,166,"For what befell you<sup>pl </sup>on the day the two armies met was with Allah’s leave, and that He may know the believers,"
  3,167,"and that He may know those who acted hypocritically when it was said to them, “Come, combat in the way of Allah, or at least defend<i>(the community) </i>.”They said, “If we knew there was going to be combat, we would follow you<sup>pl </sup>.” On that day they were closer to denial than they were to faith. They say with their mouths what is not in their hearts. But Allah knows better what they conceal."
  3,168,"Those who said of their brethren, as they stayed behind, “Had they obeyed us, they would not have been killed{1}.” Say, “Then avert death from yourselves, if you are truthful.”",footnotes:1:[Qira’at: Hisham read it as: “…they would not have been relentlessly killed.”]
  3,169,"And never{1}think<sup>sg </sup>of those killed{2}in the way of Allah as dead. Rather,<i>(they are) </i>alive, with their Lord, being provided for,",footnotes:1:[Qira’at: Hisham—in one of his recitations—read it as: “And never should he think of those killed in the…”],footnotes:2:[Qira’at: Ibn Amer read it as: “And never think<sup><small>sg</small></sup> of those relentlessly killed in the way of Allah as dead.”]
  3,170,"exulting over what Allah has brought them out of His grace and glad for those behind them who have not yet joined them: that no fear{1}shall beupon them nor shall they grieve.",footnotes:1:[Qira’at: Ya’qub read it as: “…that no fear shall ever be upon them nor shall they grieve.”]
  3,171,"Glad because of a blessing from Allah, and grace, and because Allah does not waste the reward of the believers"
  3,172,"who responded to Allah and the Messenger after the blow had befallen them. For those of them who excelled in doing good and were mindful<i>(of God) </i>is a great reward."
  3,173,"Those to whom the people said, “The people have assembled against you, so fear them.” But this only increased them in faith, and they said, “Allah is sufficient for us, and what an excellent Trustee.”"
